Text:
Pembuat dasar Bank of England, Catherine Mann mengakui Brexit telah mengakibatkan kos makanan di UK naik ke paras tertinggi dalam tempoh 45 tahun

Kadar inflasi di UK naik kepada 10.4% bagi Februari 2023, berpunca dari kekurangan bekalan makanan seperti salad di pasaran https://t.co/rK8XwyidxQ

Bank of England policy maker Catherine Mann acknowledged that Brexit has led to the cost of food in the UK to rise to the highest level in 45 years

Text: @muhdhaziqbins @nizambakeri Banjir di Selangor pun di tahap bahaya. Orang Kelantan & Terengganu turun bawa boat sebab kekurangan kelengkapan misi bantuan banjir. Tapi berbeza dengan  situasi pantai timur sekarang. Walaupun paras bahaya, kelengkapan cukup, rakyat tak panik dan bekalan makanan tersedia awal.
Translated_Tweets: @muhdhaziqbins @nizambakeri floods in Selangor are at danger. Kelantanians & amp; Terengganu came down to bring the boat due to the lack of flood relief mission. But it's different from the East Coast situation today. Despite the danger levels, the equipment is sufficient, the people are not panicked and the food supply is available early.

Text:
Lebih merisaukan baginda, cabaran besar sedang menghadapi negara sebaik sahaja tirai 2022 dilabuhkan.

Masalah ekonomi yg merudum, masalah kekurangan bekalan makanan akibat perang Ukraine dan Rusia dan juga kemungkinan berlaku banjir besar.
Translated_Tweets:
More worrying about him, the big challenge was facing the country as the curtain 2022 was overthrown.

Economic problems, the shortage of food supply due to the Ukrainian and Russian wars as well as the possibility of floods.
